(2286, 1, '2016-01-10 05:16:13', '2016-01-10 05:16:13', '<a href=\"http://testgirls/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/AcademyAudition-Flyer-Final.jpg\"><img src=\"http://testgirls/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/AcademyAudition-Flyer-Final.jpg\" alt=\"AcademyAudition-Flyer Final\" width=\"2550\" height=\"3240\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2271\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhen? January 31st, 10AM-1PM \r\nWhere? Dancemakers studio! 15 Case Goods Lane, Studio 301, Toronto, Ontario M5A 3C4\r\n\r\nGC offers different programs to cater to all levels. \r\nCalling all professional, intermediate and beginner performers seeking a supportive, driven and empowering collective to grow as individuals, and artists. We welcome all!\r\n\r\n**NEW to 2016, GC will offer 6-week cumulative beginner training programs. No audition necessary. No Dance Experience Necessary! Classes will be taught in an open and supportive environment.\r\n\r\nTo audition for all other levels, Please pre-register by sending headshots and resumes to info@thegirlsclub.ca\r\n-$5 Audition fee\r\n-$10 Audition fee for unregistered applicants and video submissions\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://testgirls/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/GIRLSCLUB-Academy.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Our Academy Brochure</a>\r\n---------------\r\nTHE ACADEMY:\r\nThe Girls Club is a distinguished Academy geared towards the development and empowerment of tomorrow’s top female performers. Our students earn industry level dance training and business leadership skills through a specialized curriculum that provides the necessary skill set to thrive in any professional environment. More importantly, we teach our students valuable audition techniques to transform their passion into a career with success & longevity. The Academy’s culture identifies with strong, passionate, and elegant leaders. Excellence is our expectation, along with focus, ambition and teamwork. Our hand-picked team represents the finest multi-disciplinary group of professional artists.\r\n\r\nFour distinct programs inspire and sustain dancers through training, exclusive access, mentorship and career opportunities. Founded over two and a half years ago, the Academy has already produced a diverse demographic of talented, intelligent women who are ready to take the industry by storm.\r\n\r\n--------------\r\n<strong><ul>\r\nOUR PROGRAMS:\r\n</ul></strong>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>GC WORKSHOP SERIES\r\n</strong><em>Beginner</em>\r\n6 week cumulative program for $175\r\nLet your sense of femininity bloom. Learn valuable confidence building skills that are transferable in many areas of life, whether in a social setting or a job interview. \r\nLearn ways to stay physically fit, and have fun doing it! \r\nClasses taught in a very open and supportive environment.\r\n\r\nSeries end showcase\r\n*No audition necessary. Email to register\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>FRESHMEN\r\n</strong><em>Dance after your competitive studio</em>\r\nBridging the gap between competitive studio training and working professionally. Learn to apply skills and techniques from your home studios to work successfully in industry level environments.\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>SOPHOMORE\r\n</strong><em>Intermediate/Advanced</em>\r\nFocus on developing style, finding and refining inner movement, and building stage presence. We also include an introduction to entertainment business and apply them in professional environments. At this level we force students to expand their comfort zone and diversify their dance vocabulary.\r\nPerformance Opportunities*Paid opportunities for members scouted to work professionally at GC\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>GC\r\n</strong><em>PROFESSIONAL</em>\r\nThe most elite level of the company. Students learn to be artists by refining their performance and leadership skills. The Girls Club doubles as a full service venue entertainment company that creates innovative, high caliber and interactive performances in various establishments. Students at this level may be chosen to perform in company bookings.\r\n\r\n*Professional Experience & Paid opportunities\r\n------------------\r\n\r\nThe Woman Behind the Club\r\n<strong>TAMINA POLLACK-PARIS</strong>\r\n<em>Founder & Executive Director\r\n</em>\r\nTamina is an industrious choreographer drawing inspiration from classic and modern influences. Her flare and attention to detail are qualities that are instilled into the nature of the academy. Adaptability and professionalism are also what creates our one-of-a-kind experience. Tamina has worked with artists such as Lady Gaga, Justin Bieber, Aloe Blacc, and Ke$ha. Her TV career includes roles in The Next Step, The Stanley Dynamic, Degrassi, Glee, American Idol, X-Factor, and Canada’s ‘So You Think You Can Dance: Season 1′. Tamina is always training and pushing herself to the limit, so she can help dancers around the world to create their own path to success.\r\n\r\n“Stay Ready, so you never have to get ready”\r\n\r\n------------------\r\n\r\n<strong>Have what it takes? \r\n</strong>Hope to see you there!\r\n\r\n#TheGirlsClub\r\n#WomenEmpoweringWomen\r\n\r\nwww.TheGirlsClub.ca', 'THE GIRLS CLUB ACADEMY AUDITIONS', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2270-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-10 05:16:13', '2016-01-10 05:16:13', '', 2270, 'http://testgirls/2270-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
