(2365, 0, '2017-03-21 04:55:41', '2017-03-21 04:55:41', '', '17267507_1392673090784341_4638053454017724416_n', 'Today\'s GC spotlight is alumni Lisa Clarke. @lala.lisaa \nApart from dance, Lisa has her own business laLa Wellness, a yoga and mindfulness program for children. She is currently working on a book titled \"I\'m growing a Yogi.\" Lisa strives to make a difference in the world and ones well being. We wish her continued success on all her endeavours. \nwww.thegirlsclub.ca\n#thegirlsclub #dance #toronto #stayready #gcacademy', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '17267507_1392673090784341_4638053454017724416_n', '', '', '2017-03-21 04:55:41', '2017-03-21 04:55:41', '', 0, 'http://testgirls/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/17267507_1392673090784341_4638053454017724416_n.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(2367, 1, '2017-04-12 00:52:40', '2017-04-12 00:52:40', 'Everything starts with a feeling.\r\n\r\nIntuitive Feels is mindful movement for the mind, body and soul. It’s a place for movers to heal, release and expand awareness through community and unity.\r\n\r\nI will be teaching students how to embody musical energy, express genuine emotion, and to release tension in our bodies. We will be connecting to our hearts, and following our unique intuitive expressions! Through the exploration of the extremities of our emotions, together we will uncover the connection between emotional and physical release.\r\n\r\nWhat to expect:\r\n• Free form movement to many genres of music to uncover their connections to our personal journeys\r\n• Group exercises to broaden our movement vocabulary, and access our emotional vulnerability\r\n• A collective group sequence at the culmination of class\r\n\r\n*This class will be taught at a beginner level. No dance experience necessary, just a love for music, movement, and honest vibes!*\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nExchange: $20\r\nAlternity members: FREE\r\nhttps://www.alter8.com/pages/members\r\n\r\nArrive early for healthy drinks at the elixir bar before the event!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nABOUT TAMINA\r\nFresh off the superbowl field with Lady Gaga, Tamina Pollack-Paris has worked with music\'s biggest names, such as Justin Bieber, Aloe Blacc, and Ke$ha. Her TV career includes roles in The Next Step, The Stanley Dynamic, Degrassi, Glee, American Idol, X-Factor, Canada’s So You Think You Can Dance: Season 1. Tamina is always training and pushing herself to the limit, so she can influence others to follow their dreams.\r\n\r\nWith Toronto never far from her heart, Tamina wanted to find an avenue of giving back to the community that meant so much to her. That vision grew into The Girls Club, which is now a distinguished Academy that empowers tomorrow’s top performers through a specialized performance and business curriculum. Eager to spread the knowledge she’s gained over the years, Tamina has decided to branch out and offer open classes that nourish the soul through music and movement.\r\n\r\nFor more information on Tamina or The Girls Club, please visit: www.thegirlsclub.ca | Instagram: @intuitivefeels', 'Intuitive Feels', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'intuitive-feels', '', '', '2017-04-12 00:52:40', '2017-04-12 00:52:40', '', 0, 'http://testgirls/?page_id=2367', 0, 'page', '', 0),
